{"cells":[{"cell_type":"markdown","source":["# Evaluating the Performance of Linear Regression Models\n","\n","To obtain an unbiased estimate of a model's generalization performance, it is crucial to split the dataset into separate training and test datasets. The model is fit on the training data and evaluated on the unseen test data.\n","\n","## 1. Setting up a Multiple Regression Model\n","\n","First, we split the dataset and train a multiple regression model using multiple features."],"metadata":{"id":"dall1tPkVu4B"}},{"cell_type":"code","source":["import pandas as pd\n","\n","# Define the subset of columns to use\n","columns = ['Overall Qual', 'Overall Cond', 'Gr Liv Area',\n","           'Central Air', 'Total Bsmt SF', 'SalePrice']\n","\n","# Load the dataset\n","df = pd.read_csv('http://jse.amstat.org/v19n3/decock/AmesHousing.txt',\n","                 sep='\\t',\n","                 usecols=columns)\n","\n","# Map string categorical variables to integers\n","df['Central Air'] = df['Central Air'].map({'N': 0, 'Y': 1})\n","\n","# Drop rows containing missing values (Total Bsmt SF has 1 missing value)\n","df = df.dropna(axis=0)"],"metadata":{"id":"52dsBlEeWXc6","executionInfo":{"status":"ok","timestamp":1781863883754,"user_tz":-330,"elapsed":192,"user":{"displayName":"Gobisan Ananthanadarajan","userId":"08370486503672403873"}}},"execution_count":10,"outputs":[]},{"cell_type":"code","source":["from sklearn.model_selection import train_test_split\n","from sklearn.linear_model import LinearRegression\n","import numpy as np\n","\n","target = 'SalePrice'\n","features = df.columns[df.columns != target]\n","X = df[features].values\n","y = df[target].values\n","\n","X_train, X_test, y_train, y_test = train_test_split(\n","    X, y, test_size=0.3, random_state=123)\n","\n","slr = LinearRegression()\n","slr.fit(X_train, y_train)\n","\n","y_train_pred = slr.predict(X_train)\n","y_test_pred = slr.predict(X_test)"],"outputs":[],"execution_count":11,"metadata":{"id":"iiw-crdkVu4E","executionInfo":{"status":"ok","timestamp":1781863883756,"user_tz":-330,"elapsed":1,"user":{"displayName":"Gobisan Ananthanadarajan","userId":"08370486503672403873"}}}},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":["## 2. Residual Plots\n","\n","Because multiple regression cannot be easily visualized in a 2D plot, **residual plots** are used. Residuals are the differences (vertical distances) between the actual and predicted values. Plotting these against predicted values helps diagnose:\n","\n","* Nonlinearity\n","* Outliers\n","* Whether errors are randomly distributed (a good model should have randomly scattered errors around the centerline)."],"metadata":{"id":"WUmNNHuwVu4F"}},{"cell_type":"code","source":["import matplotlib.pyplot as plt\n","\n","x_max = np.max([np.max(y_train_pred), np.max(y_test_pred)])\n","x_min = np.min([np.min(y_train_pred), np.min(y_test_pred)])\n","\n","fig, (ax1, ax2) = plt.subplots(1, 2, figsize=(7, 3), sharey=True)\n","\n","ax1.scatter(y_test_pred, y_test_pred - y_test,\n","            c='limegreen', marker='s', edgecolor='white',\n","            label='Test data')\n","\n","ax2.scatter(y_train_pred, y_train_pred - y_train,\n","            c='steelblue', marker='o', edgecolor='white',\n","            label='Training data')\n","\n","ax1.set_ylabel('Residuals')\n","\n","for ax in (ax1, ax2):\n","    ax.set_xlabel('Predicted values')\n","    ax.legend(loc='upper left')\n","    ax.hlines(y=0, xmin=x_min-100, xmax=x_max+100, color='black', lw=2)\n","\n","plt.tight_layout()\n","plt.show()"],"outputs":[{"output_type":"display_data","data":{"text/plain":["<Figure size 700x300 with 2 Axes>"],"image/png":"\n"},"metadata":{}}],"execution_count":12,"metadata":{"colab":{"base_uri":"https://localhost:8080/","height":307},"id":"K8GSzvZBVu4G","executionInfo":{"status":"ok","timestamp":1781863884063,"user_tz":-330,"elapsed":306,"user":{"displayName":"Gobisan Ananthanadarajan","userId":"08370486503672403873"}},"outputId":"905509f6-7bed-416e-fbc1-576a544d0112"}},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":["## 3. Mean Squared Error (MSE)\n","\n","MSE is a useful quantitative measure of a model's performance, representing the average squared difference between the estimated values and the actual value. It is the loss function minimized to fit the linear regression model (without the $\\frac{1}{2}$ scaling factor used in gradient descent).\n","\n","$$MSE = \\frac{1}{n}\\sum_{i=1}^{n}(y^{(i)} - \\hat{y}^{(i)})^2$$"],"metadata":{"id":"QBBm7gx4Vu4G"}},{"cell_type":"code","source":["from sklearn.metrics import mean_squared_error\n","\n","mse_train = mean_squared_error(y_train, y_train_pred)\n","mse_test = mean_squared_error(y_test, y_test_pred)\n","\n","print(f'MSE train: {mse_train:.2f}')\n","print(f'MSE test: {mse_test:.2f}')"],"outputs":[{"output_type":"stream","name":"stdout","text":["MSE train: 1497216245.85\n","MSE test: 1516565821.00\n"]}],"execution_count":13,"metadata":{"colab":{"base_uri":"https://localhost:8080/"},"id":"Q0bzaWGWVu4G","executionInfo":{"status":"ok","timestamp":1781863884075,"user_tz":-330,"elapsed":8,"user":{"displayName":"Gobisan Ananthanadarajan","userId":"08370486503672403873"}},"outputId":"edd351ab-da18-438a-d7fd-718441d72438"}},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":["## 4. Mean Absolute Error (MAE)\n","\n","MSE normalizes by sample size, making it comparable across different sample sizes. However, showing the error on the original unit scale is often more intuitive. You can use the root mean squared error or the **Mean Absolute Error (MAE)**, which is slightly less sensitive to outliers.\n","\n","$$MAE = \\frac{1}{n}\\sum_{i=1}^{n}|y^{(i)} - \\hat{y}^{(i)}|$$"],"metadata":{"id":"eroeJOidVu4H"}},{"cell_type":"code","source":["from sklearn.metrics import mean_absolute_error\n","\n","mae_train = mean_absolute_error(y_train, y_train_pred)\n","mae_test = mean_absolute_error(y_test, y_test_pred)\n","\n","print(f'MAE train: {mae_train:.2f}')\n","print(f'MAE test: {mae_test:.2f}')"],"outputs":[{"output_type":"stream","name":"stdout","text":["MAE train: 25983.03\n","MAE test: 24921.29\n"]}],"execution_count":14,"metadata":{"colab":{"base_uri":"https://localhost:8080/"},"id":"Nv9M_vi4Vu4H","executionInfo":{"status":"ok","timestamp":1781863884077,"user_tz":-330,"elapsed":2,"user":{"displayName":"Gobisan Ananthanadarajan","userId":"08370486503672403873"}},"outputId":"a212342e-07ac-48bd-aff9-367686449434"}},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":["## 5. Coefficient of Determination ($R^2$)\n","\n","MAE and MSE are unbounded and their interpretation depends on dataset scaling. The **Coefficient of Determination ($R^2$)** is a standardized version of the MSE that is bounded and better for interpretability. It represents the fraction of response variance captured by the model.\n","\n","$$R^2 = 1 - \\frac{SSE}{SST}$$\n","\n","Where **SSE** is the sum of squared errors:\n","\n","\n","$$SSE = \\sum_{i=1}^{n}(y^{(i)} - \\hat{y}^{(i)})^2$$\n","\n","And **SST** is the total sum of squares (the variance of the response):\n","\n","\n","$$SST = \\sum_{i=1}^{n}(y^{(i)} - \\mu_y)^2$$\n","\n","$R^2$ is simply a rescaled version of the MSE:\n","\n","\n","$$R^2 = 1 - \\frac{\\frac{1}{n}SSE}{\\frac{1}{n}SST} = 1 - \\frac{\\frac{1}{n}\\sum_{i=1}^{n}(y^{(i)} - \\hat{y}^{(i)})^2}{\\frac{1}{n}\\sum_{i=1}^{n}(y^{(i)} - \\mu_y)^2} = 1 - \\frac{MSE}{Var(y)}$$\n","\n","* For training data, $R^2$ is bounded between 0 and 1.\n","* For test data, $R^2$ can be negative (indicating extreme overfitting or unscaled test sets). An $R^2$ of 1 means perfect prediction."],"metadata":{"id":"Rdx6m70jVu4H"}},{"cell_type":"code","source":["from sklearn.metrics import r2_score\n","\n","train_r2 = r2_score(y_train, y_train_pred)\n","test_r2 = r2_score(y_test, y_test_pred)\n","\n","print(f'R^2 train: {train_r2:.3f}, test: {test_r2:.3f}')"],"outputs":[{"output_type":"stream","name":"stdout","text":["R^2 train: 0.769, test: 0.752\n"]}],"execution_count":15,"metadata":{"colab":{"base_uri":"https://localhost:8080/"},"id":"C94Cm4m8Vu4H","executionInfo":{"status":"ok","timestamp":1781863884089,"user_tz":-330,"elapsed":11,"user":{"displayName":"Gobisan Ananthanadarajan","userId":"08370486503672403873"}},"outputId":"f4b7242d-36e0-49e4-c36d-9d3c552a08b5"}},{"cell_type":"code","source":[],"metadata":{"id":"tEr4Q2xUXRc9","executionInfo":{"status":"ok","timestamp":1781863884089,"user_tz":-330,"elapsed":1,"user":{"displayName":"Gobisan Ananthanadarajan","userId":"08370486503672403873"}}},"execution_count":15,"outputs":[]}],"metadata":{"colab":{"provenance":[]},"kernelspec":{"display_name":"Python 3","name":"python3"}},"nbformat":4,"nbformat_minor":0}